\title{Remove rewrite rules for extensionality principles}
\tag{changelog}

\p{
We remove the rewrite rules for `funext-redex`, `ua-linv`, and `IdSJ-refl`. These
gave judgmental computation rules for function extensionality, univalence, and the
`J`-rule of an arbitrary identity system: `happly (funextâ†’ p)` used to reduce to `p`,
`equivâ†گId (ua p)` used to reduce to `p`, and `IdSJ P Pâ‚€ IdSâ‚€` used to reduce to `Pâ‚€`.
Now we instead explicitly reason about these principles.
}
